President Barack Obama has proclaimed April 10-16, 2011, as National Volunteer Week in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of volunteers and their contributions to various sectors such as education, healthcare, and disaster relief. He emphasizes that volunteers play a crucial role in improving communities and encourages all Americans to get involved in service projects. The President also mentions the government's commitment to investing in community solutions and increasing opportunities for Americans to serve through programs like Senior Corps, AmeriCorps, and Learn and Serve America. He urges citizens to visit www.Serve.gov to find local volunteer opportunities and make service a part of their daily lives.